<P>VI. Next, C. O. is hugely di&s;plea&s;ed with
A. P. becau&s;e he has broughta <HI>Demon&s;trati|on</HI>
for the <HI>Exi&s;tence</HI> of a <HI>Deity,</HI> from the Im|po&s;&s;ibility
of the <HI>Mechanical</HI> Production of
<HI>Animals,</HI> and alledges the proof is not Good,
