C. O. is able to di&s;tingui&s;h betwixt things;
The Rea&s;on of which is, that he is not capable
of entring into the Inward Nature of the
Matters he &s;peaks about: Like a true <HI>Quack</HI>
he keeps you at a great di&s;tance from the
