<HI>C. O</HI>'s Frailties: No hone&s;t Man wou'd lay
out his Pains in confuting any of the &s;everal
<PB N="34" REF="47">
ways of <HI>Demon&s;trating</HI> the Being of a <HI>GOD;</HI>
The more they are, the better; For &s;ome are
to be wrought upon one way; o hers ano|ther.</P>
<P>But &s;ays <HI>C. O. Malbranch</HI> and <HI>Bellini</HI> have
both of 'em <HI>Demon&s;trated</HI> the <HI>Immechanical</HI>
