<HI>Species.</HI></P>
<P><PB N="36" REF="49">
<HI>C. O.</HI> &s;aw very well that if <HI>Lew$en|hoeck's</HI>
Te&s;timony were admitted, of his
havng con&s;tantly ob&s;erved an Infinity of
<HI>Animalculs</HI> in the Male-&s;eed of all the Crea|tures
he had occa&s;ion to examin, this wou'd
be an <HI>Ocular Demon&s;tration</HI> of <HI>A. P</HI>'s Infe|rence;
He therefore ab&s;olutly denys the
Matter of fact, and re&s;olves the whole into
a meer <HI>Deceptio vi&s;us;</HI> It being no other
(&s;ays he) <HI>Quam particularum liquoris &s;e|mina$s
in liquamen tenuius fati&s;centis, luc|ta
&amp; di&s;tractio.</HI> I &s;uppo&s;e he means (if one
can &s;uppo&s;e him capable of a meaning) that
